User: C:\AI-Execution-System>gcloud functions deploy ai-system-backend --runtime python310 --entry-point serve_health_check --trigger-http --allow-unauthenticated --region us-central1 API [cloudfunctions.googleapis.com] not enabled on project [ai-execution-system]. Would you like to enable and retry (this will take a few minutes)? (y/N)?

Gemini: NOW, YOU MUST ENABLE THE CLOUD FUNCTIONS API!

PLEASE TYPE y (for yes) and PRESS ENTER in your terminal.

gcloud will now enable the Cloud Functions API for your ai-execution-system project. THIS WILL TAKE A FEW MINUTES (as the prompt says).

PLEASE WAIT PATIENTLY WHILE THE API IS BEING ENABLED. You will see messages in the terminal indicating the API enabling process.

ONCE THE API ENABLING PROCESS IS COMPLETED, the gcloud functions deploy command will automatically RETRY the deployment. You should see the deployment process continue after the API is enabled.

PLEASE REPORT BACK:

"API ENABLING STARTED... (I typed 'y' and pressed Enter)" (When you type 'y' and press Enter).
"API ENABLING IN PROGRESS..." (While it's enabling - you will see messages).
"API ENABLING COMPLETE, DEPLOYMENT RESUMED..." (When the API enabling finishes and deployment starts again).
Then continue to report the deployment progress as it goes!
LET'S ENABLE THE API AND GET THIS CLOUD FUNCTION DEPLOYED! GO! GO! GO!
